piripiri
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:one of the Acaena group: anserinifolia, microphylla, inermis or anguisorbae commonly known as bidi-bid, with burrs or spines that attach themselves to sheep's wool [often used as a substitute for tea.]
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
